social_posts.post_text: Own BOTH books I’ve authored? Or only the first? Preorder my new title AIM HIGH, LITTLE GIANT, AIM HIGH! at link in bio and @wearelittlegiants NOW! Release date is Monday :) Photo of me on set at NYC POINT GODS by @chadgittens

Growing up, I didn’t have books written by people I could identify with, much less characters I could imagine myself being in a positive and affirming way. I wrote AIM HIGH, LITTLE GIANT, AIM HIGH! for @wearelittlegiants to reach current and future generations of kids of color who may be into the experiences that I cherish providing to my own son now, with a progressive lens and entry points for parents of multiple backgrounds. I am PROUD of this project!!! Please consider supporting the title at the link in my bio or aimhighlittlegiant.com Wooord

Shorty is reading my new book in LA! @wearelittlegiants is the first shop out there to carry AIM HIGH, LITTLE GIANT, AIM HIGH! Buy online at link in my bio or aimhighlittlegiant.com Big up @a1espino @jillcee @eve_eames for letting me post this moment!

My kids book drops today! The story is about Taina, a nine-year-old Afro Boricua b-ball novice growing up in Brooklyn during a pandemic who learns valuable life lessons from family, friends, and community, both on and off the court. Grab the first edition at the link in my bio or aimhighlittlegiant.com Written for ages 7+ but lovers of fiction, diversity, social justice, social-emotional learning, unschooling, and goofy humor would all love the narrative and are welcome to read as well :) Published by @wearelittlegiants Ilustrado por Estefanía Rivera Cortés (@peptidolinear) de Santurce, Puerto Rico

TRIKE1 hit me, “Read your kids book … twice. Love it!” then the graf legend shared this illustration he drew inspired by AIM HIGH, LITTLE GIANT, AIM HIGH! which you too can order now at the link in my bio or aimhighlittlegiant.com, yo! Follow TRIKE1 at @nyc.graffiti.portal for incredible firsthand history of aerosol art in NY and beyond. Also peep his  @riverdalesummerleague for HS kids (which gets repped in the drawing).

LOVE @romanperez4 for reading my new book to the youth at the @dudobaez @officialteamfirst @give.n.gonyc Saturday workout! Published by @wearelittlegiants, AIM HIGH, LITTLE GIANT, AIM HIGH! is available at the link in my bio and aimhighlittlegiant.com I wrote the narrative exactly for a diverse audience like this one in the BX. Also amped because to my knowledge, Roman’s the first educator to read the title publicly. Kaboom!

Only three of 50+ bookshops I’ve called has ordered my new book, so I’m SUPER GRATEFUL to my record store, hip hop/kicks/b-ball community for distributing the hard cover to the dear readers I want to reach! Hit link in bio or aimhighlittlegiant.com to see our BUY LOCAL list which includes @the.shopnyc @kaydeerecords @luckyrecordsmiami @moodsmusic @e14gallery @concoursecoffee @thespotgeneva @wordupbooks @premiumgoodshtx @wearelittlegiants @quincy.james.vintage The first two bookstores to carry the title were @libros787 @juliadeburgosbookstore, both Boricua owned! Agradecido. Can’t forget to show love to my fam who have shown overwhelming support with spreading love, especially @kennyblend for the video and @back2basicsnyc @growourgame @dudobaez @romanperez4 for passing out the first edition to their players. If you want to order a quantity for your program, camp, school, group, center, whatever, DM me! I’m not dependent on the publishing world who has not shown me light so far. I’m doing this out the trunk ‘90s street team vibes! “You know my steeeeez …”

What’s your favorite De La song ever? Mine is “Buddy” lp version! @stretcharmstrong and I play two hours of  their music Friday 2/17 12-2pm EST on @applemusic to show LOVE to Dave aka Trugoy who passed this week. Mucho strength to his fam, Pos, Maceo, and my man @danteross who played me their unreleased/unmastered debut album months before it dropped back in 1989. That moment literally changed the course of my life, as was then that I realized I would love to work in the music industry. Dante was A&R at Tommy Boy Records, but had started at Rush as a messenger. That became my blueprint, and I followed those same steps. So I’m forever grateful to him but also to De La for being the inspirational score music to my turning point of going from listener to behind the scenes hip hop cat. Wooooord Photo by @tamaraschlesinger taken at @wkcr the same night Big L ripped our mic to shreds! L came up five to six times, and each was as ferocious as the legendary one with Jay. Rest in peace to L and Plug 2. Crazy

Wanna work on your game with me today? Join me for a virtual Basics to Boogie at 12:15pm EST! All levels/ages welcome. FREE! DM for Zoom link and info :) Photo taken in 2010 at a @hoops4hopeglobal clinic I led in Harare, Zimbabwe where they had recently dedicated the court in my name for the advocacy I had provided for the non-profit work they do. Woooooord

Playing my @thegodrakim interview from ‘97 on www.Twitch.tv/koolboblove off cassette right now until 6:45pm! Originally recorded for Stress Magazine and was the cover feature. We were in his car so audio was not clean, but he shared some gems and a lot of math!
Me and @stretcharmstrong rock “De La Love” 6-8pm EST on @applemusic hits radio! Bless Dave’s energy, exist in power, fam

Wanna hear my 1996 Tito Puente interview from @vibemagazine? Tune in to www.twitch.tv/koolboblove at 9:30am EST! I'm also playing my @officialrobertaflack interview afterwards which is on the b-side of the cassette. Yes. Analog recording. That's how we did it in the '90s, ha ha! I also used to drive my editors crazy cuz I didn't have a computer, typewriter, or fax machine, so I'd hand write my transcriptions, then ride my bike up to the office to drop it off. Gotta love those days, ha ha :) Photo: @tamaraschlesinger
What song starts your Happy Monday? Build An Ark “In The Park” got me OPEN! Good looks @rushhourstore for releasing the Anthology on vinyl. Kaboom sauce

@stretcharmstrong and I were inducted into the NAB Hall of Fame! Here’s my acceptance speech (since I couldn’t be on stage with my boy at the ceremony in Las Vegas today). Toooo many people to thank who I didn’t mention here because they only gave me two minutes on mic, but forever grateful to @danteross for inspiring me to enter the music industry, @emceeserch @rushtown298 @davidjgossett for getting me my first job at @defjam which was where I met Stretch. So without these four people, I would have never eventually gotten on air. And eternal LOVE to Adrian Bartos for giving me a career in broadcasting. Literally. 1990 on forward, big up @wkcr for the platform, every artist who ever blessed our mics, and equal stats to every listener worldwide who ever tuned in. Without our community, me and Stretch would have been making dope tapes for ourselves to listen to, but no impact beyond. Appreciate @wearebroadcasters for the shine, too. Mad more heads to thank, but I’ll pause there. Thanks yo!

Sometimes I really don't know what to say, or feel. While I smile in a safe home, and am thankful for that blessing daily, I'm fully aware that we lose precious lives to war, mass shootings, hate crimes, climate disasters, disease spread, and other causes. I watch, read, and absorb. To those directly afflicted this month, I can't imagine the pain. I've lost three friends in the last week, and I just thought that's light compared for example to the Palestinian journalist who senselessly lost his whole family. Gone. F*ck. I've been a reporter, a documentarian, a TV/radio host, all in peaceful environments, so I can't identify what it's like to be a combat zone, but... sh*t, the news of that death struck me. And I hope that somehow, someway, at some point, lawmakers, politicians, authorities, governments, etc. can also empathize--then make changes as a result of compassion. Ceasefire in Gaza for the immediate situation, and long term fair solutions for all humanity that are sustainable and reachable, however difficult it may be to climb there. I hope I'm making sense here. I know this is a delicate time. I've been self conscious posting about new books/merchandise, radio shows, anniversaries, etc. the last few days when there is so much negative insanity going on. So... just having a stream of consciousness moment right now. The pursuit of happiness is a global human right. May we all see the day when that can be realized, not just for me, not just for public figures, not just for certain communities of people, not just for certain areas of the world. Everyone. Everywhere. Written with love.

This week we had to change the course. This was needed and we understand what the culture needs. Every Player Counts was created to open the platform for many who have impacted the game from every angle. It’s our pleasure to present Robert “Bobbito” Garcia, also known as DJ Cucumber Slice and Kool Bob Love, is an American DJ, author, streetball player, streetball coach, and member of the Rock Steady Crew. He is known as a former co-host of hip hop radio show The Stretch Armstrong and Bobbito Show, alongside Adrian “Stretch Armstrong” Bartos, from 1990 until 1999. Bobbito has created a lane within NYC basketball like no other. Let’s give our attention to the legend Bobbito Garcia on this is Every Player Counts!!!

Robert “Bobbito” Garcia
